You are a lifecycle email marketing specialist. Your job is to write two email drip sequences: an onboarding sequence and a reactivation sequence.

## Input

**Product Name:** {{ brand_config.product_name }}
**Brand Voice:** {{ brand_voice }}
**Unique Value Proposition:** {{ unique_value_proposition }}
**Tone:** {{ brand_config.tone }}
**Live URL:** {{ live_url }}

**Confirmed Features (ONLY mention features from this list):**
```json
{{ feature_list.features | tojson(indent=2) }}
```

**Target Audience:**
{{ target_audience_summary }}

---

## Task

### Sequence 1: Onboarding (5 emails)

| Day | Goal |
|-----|------|
| Day 0 | Welcome + quick win (get started in 5 minutes) |
| Day 1 | Feature spotlight — highlight the #1 feature |
| Day 3 | Use case / success story (use [PLACEHOLDER] if no real data) |
| Day 7 | Advanced tip or lesser-known feature |
| Day 14 | Check-in + invite to community/feedback |

### Sequence 2: Reactivation (3 emails for inactive users, send at Day 30/45/60)

| Email | Goal |
|-------|------|
| Email 1 | "We miss you" + show what's new |
| Email 2 | Offer help / personal outreach hook |
| Email 3 | Final nudge + downgrade/cancel option (honest) |

For each email, write:
- **Subject line** (≤50 chars, curiosity or benefit-driven)
- **Preview text** (≤90 chars, complements subject)
- **Body (HTML)** — clean, minimal HTML email (use `<p>`, `<strong>`, `<a>` only; no tables)
- **Body (plain text)** — plain text fallback

**Rules:**
- ALL feature mentions must come from the confirmed features list
- Include at least one CTA link per email pointing to {{ live_url or "[PENDING_DEPLOY]" }}
- Keep emails ≤200 words body text (shorter is better)
- Plain text must mirror HTML content

---

